, male genitalia. A, C, D—posterior view; B—lateral view; E—posterolateral view. Abbreviations: aa—aedeagal apodeme, al a ss—anterior lobe of anterior surstylus, ce—cercus, ep—epandrium, hy—hypandrium, pl a ss—posterior lobe of anterior surstylus, p ss—posterior surstylus, sp—setose process on anterior lobe of anterior surstylus.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="FACD9A97FFFBFFE5FF35F900FABCE9CC" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2599021/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" startId="3.[151,244,1724,1746]" targetBox="[166,1436,191,1703]" targetPageId="3">
