<paragraph id="AE0DCA1FFFFBFFE2FF65F8A6FB0BEC07" blockId="3.[151,1436,1818,2015]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,804]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="591" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFBFFE5FF65F8A6FE1CE812" bold="true" box="[199,421,1818,1841]" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">Taxonomy position.</emphasis>
With a short midfrontal stripe not extending beyond the middle of the frons and an unpatterned wing, 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFBFFE5FF42F881FED0E877" authorityName="Rozkosny" authorityYear="1991" box="[224,361,1852,1876]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shatalkini">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFBFFE5FF42F881FED0E877" box="[224,361,1852,1876]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">P. shatalkini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
keys to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFBFFE5FDD6F880FC7CE870" authority="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1830" box="[628,965,1852,1876]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Chetocera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFBFFE5FDD6F880FD5AE877" box="[628,739,1852,1876]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">Chetocera</emphasis>
Robineau-Desvoidy
</taxonomicName>
(including 22 species in the Palaearctic) according to 
<bibRefCitation id="CA23B7EEFFFBFFE5FE86F8E3FE49E855" author="Rozkosny, R." box="[292,496,1887,1910]" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" pagination="384 - 390" refId="ref2691" refString="Rozkosny, R. (1964) Zur Taxonomie der Gattung Pherbellia Robineau-Desvoidy (Diptera, Sciomyzidae). Acta Societatis Entomologicae Cechosloveniae, 61 (4), 384 - 390." type="journal article" year="1964">Rozkošný’s (1964)</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFBFFE5FE55F8E2FDD1E855" authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1830" box="[503,616,1886,1910]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFBFFE5FE55F8E2FDD1E855" box="[503,616,1886,1910]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">Pherbellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
delineation in seven subgenera. Following Steyskal’s delineation of species groups of 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFBFFE5FEA7F83DFECFE8BA" authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1830" box="[261,374,1921,1945]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFBFFE5FEA7F83DFECFE8BA" box="[261,374,1921,1945]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">Pherbellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="CA23B7EEFFFBFFE5FE27F83EFD99E8BA" author="Steyskal, G. C." box="[389,544,1922,1945]" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" pagination="173 - 180" refId="ref2810" refString="Steyskal, G. C. (1949) New Diptera from Michigan (Stratiomyidae, Sarcophagidae, Sciomyzidae). Papers of the Michigan Academy of Science, Arts and Letters, 33 (2), 173 - 180." type="journal article" year="1949">Steyskal 1949</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="CA23B7EEFFFBFFE5FD8EF83EFDDAE8BA" author="Steyskal, G. C." box="[556,611,1922,1945]" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" pagination="405 - 415" refId="ref2852" refString="Steyskal, G. C. (1961) The North American Sciomyzidae related to Pherbellia fuscipes (Macquart) (Diptera: Acalyptratae). Papers of the Michigan Academy of Science, Arts and Letters, 46, 405 - 415." type="journal article" year="1961">1961</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="CA23B7EEFFFBFFE5FDD2F83EFD11E8BA" author="Steyskal, G. C." box="[624,680,1922,1945]" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" pagination="113 - 125" refId="ref2896" refString="Steyskal, G. C. (1963) Taxonomic notes on Sciomyzidae (Diptera, Acalyptratae). Papers of the Michigan Academy of Science, Arts and Letters, 48, 113 - 125." type="journal article" year="1963">1963</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="CA23B7EEFFFBFFE5FD11F83EFD55E8BA" author="Steyskal, G. C." box="[691,748,1922,1945]" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" pagination="31 - 36" refId="ref2933" refString="Steyskal, G. C. (1966) [1965]. The Nearctic species of Pherbellia Robineau-Desvoidy, subgenus Oxytaenia Sack (Diptera: Sciomyzidae). Papers of the Michigan Academy of Science, Arts and Letters, 51, 31 - 36." type="journal article" year="1966">1966</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFBFFE5FCA2F83EFC3DE8BA" authorityName="Rozkosny" authorityYear="1991" box="[768,900,1921,1945]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shatalkini">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFBFFE5FCA2F83EFC3DE8BA" box="[768,900,1921,1945]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">P. shatalkini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in the group of species with a short midfrontal stripe, two fronto-orbital setae, and a “hairy” anepisternum. 
<bibRefCitation id="CA23B7EEFFFBFFE5FC81F818FC65E898" author="Rozkosny, R." box="[803,988,1956,1979]" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" pagination="391 - 406" refId="ref2724" refString="Rozkosny, R. (1991) A key to the Palaearctic species of Pherbellia Robineau-Desvoidy, with descriptions of three new species (Diptera, Sciomyzidae). Acta Entomologica Bohemoslovaca, 88, 391 - 406." type="journal article" year="1991">Rozkošný (1991)</bibRefCitation>
did not name them as a group, but in his key to species with that combination of characters [except for a long midfrontal stripe in 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFBFFE5FB26F874FADEE8FD" authority="(Hendel)" authorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[1156,1383,1990,2015]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mikiana">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFBFFE5FB26F874FB41E8FD" box="[1156,1272,1990,2015]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">P. mikiana</emphasis>
(Hendel)
</taxonomicName>
], the species 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FF4EFF24FEE6EF8C" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[236,351,151,175]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mikiana">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FF4EFF24FEE6EF8C" box="[236,351,151,175]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. mikiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FECCFF24FDF8EF8C" authority="(Hendel)" authorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[366,577,152,175]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="czernyi">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FECCFF24FE6EEF8C" box="[366,471,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. czernyi</emphasis>
(Hendel)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FDECFF24FCACEF8C" authority="(Hendel)" authorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[590,789,151,175]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FDECFF24FD12EF8C" box="[590,683,151,175]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. pilosa</emphasis>
(Hendel)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FCF3FF24FC6FEF8C" authorityName="Rozkosny" authorityYear="1991" box="[849,982,151,175]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shatalkini">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FCF3FF24FC6FEF8C" box="[849,982,151,175]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. shatalkini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appear together. Among these species, 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FA2AFF24FF54EFF2" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1900" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mikiana">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FA2AFF24FF54EFF2" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. mikiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Mediterranean and coastal western Palaearctic) is distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FC1EFF06FBFBEFF2" authorityName="Rozkosny" authorityYear="1991" box="[956,1090,185,209]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shatalkini">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FC1EFF06FBFBEFF2" box="[956,1090,185,209]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. shatalkini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the midfrontal stripe reaching the anterior margin of the frons, vein M 
<subScript id="3236C85AFFFCFFE2FD0CFF50FD7DEFDB" attach="left" box="[686,708,236,248]" fontSize="5" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">1+2</subScript>
with a stump vein, infuscated crossveins, a completely black basal flagellomere, and in major male postabdominal characters, especially peglike setae on the anterior surstylus. As in 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FA2AFEBEFEB9EE1F" authorityName="Rozkosny" authorityYear="1991" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shatalkini">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FA2AFEBEFEB9EE1F" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. shatalkini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FEB3FE99FEC5EE1F" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[273,380,293,316]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="czernyi">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FEB3FE99FEC5EE1F" box="[273,380,293,316]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. czernyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Central European) has a short midfrontal stripe and lacks a stump vein on vein M 
<subScript id="3236C85AFFFCFFE2FA85FE88FA84EE63" attach="left" box="[1319,1341,308,320]" fontSize="5" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">1+2</subScript>
, but the anepisternum has only 10–12 hair-like setulae (many minute setulae on posterior half in 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FBF9FEF6FB66EE42" authorityName="Rozkosny" authorityYear="1991" box="[1115,1247,329,353]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shatalkini">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FBF9FEF6FB66EE42" box="[1115,1247,329,353]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. shatalkini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), all basitarsi are contrasting white (brown in 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FE67FED1FDF0EEA7" authorityName="Rozkosny" authorityYear="1991" box="[453,585,364,388]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shatalkini">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FE67FED1FDF0EEA7" box="[453,585,364,388]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. shatalkini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), both surstyli are elongate and rather simple (anterior surstylus consists of two lobes in 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FF50FE2CFECCEE84" authorityName="Rozkosny" authorityYear="1991" box="[242,373,399,423]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shatalkini">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FF50FE2CFECCEE84" box="[242,373,399,423]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. shatalkini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the hind femora are densely haired ventrally (with three strong setae anterodorsally deviating from other setosity in 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FE29FE0EFDA9EEEA" authorityName="Rozkosny" authorityYear="1991" box="[395,528,433,457]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shatalkini">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FE29FE0EFDA9EEEA" box="[395,528,433,457]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. shatalkini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FD8AFE0DFD5BEEEA" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[552,738,433,457]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FD8AFE0DFD5BEEEA" box="[552,738,433,457]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Pherbellia pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(South Mediterranean Europe, Near East, Central Asia) has the fore basitarsus slightly paler than the rest of the tarsus (entirely brown in 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FC06FE69FB9EEECF" authorityName="Rozkosny" authorityYear="1991" box="[932,1063,468,492]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shatalkini">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FC06FE69FB9EEECF" box="[932,1063,468,492]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. shatalkini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), fore coxa with many setae above the middle (with only two setae in 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FDBCFE44FD1DED2C" authorityName="Rozkosny" authorityYear="1991" box="[542,676,503,527]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shatalkini">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FDBCFE44FD1DED2C" box="[542,676,503,527]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. shatalkini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and anterior part of anterior surstylus clublike, very densely setose across the apex (with strongly sclerotized square projection in 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FC9EFDA6FC78ED12" authorityName="Rozkosny" authorityYear="1991" box="[828,961,537,561]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shatalkini">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FC9EFDA6FC78ED12" box="[828,961,537,561]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. shatalkini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FC7AFDA5FB03ED12" authorityName="Rozkosny" authorityYear="1991" box="[984,1210,537,561]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shatalkini">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FC7AFDA5FB03ED12" box="[984,1210,537,561]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Pherbellia shatalkini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more similar to 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FA2AFDA6FEFCED77" authority="Steyskal" authorityName="Steyskal" authorityYear="1963" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frohnei">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FA2AFDA6FF5AED77" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. frohnei</emphasis>
Steyskal
</taxonomicName>
(Naknek, 
<collectingRegion id="6C7604FDFFFCFFE2FE15FD81FDBDED77" box="[439,516,573,596]" country="United States of America" name="Alaska" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Alaska</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="D6A58A8FFFFCFFE2FDB2FD81FDE3ED77" box="[528,602,573,596]" name="United States of America" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">U.S.A.</collectingCountry>
) but differs especially in features of the male postabdomen. In 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FAAEFD81FACAED77" authorityName="Steyskal" authorityYear="1963" box="[1292,1395,572,596]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frohnei">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FAAEFD81FACAED77" box="[1292,1395,572,596]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. frohnei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the anterior lobe of the anterior surstylus has a group of six or seven setae on the postero-mesial corner, not on a spatulate, sclerotized process, and about six strong marginal setae arising at midlength on the anterior surface of the anterior lobe as in 
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FF17FD19FEFAED9F" box="[181,323,676,700]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FF17FD19FE86ED9F" authorityName="Rozkosny" authorityYear="1991" box="[181,319,676,700]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shatalkini">P. shatalkini</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
In 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FEC9FD19FE6DED9F" authorityName="Steyskal" authorityYear="1963" box="[363,468,676,700]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frohnei">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FEC9FD19FE6DED9F" box="[363,468,676,700]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. frohnei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the anterior lobe has a short anteroventral process, according to the figure by 
<bibRefCitation id="CA23B7EEFFFCFFE2FAE3FD19FE9CEDFC" author="Steyskal, G. C." pageId="4" pageNumber="591" pagination="113 - 125" refId="ref2896" refString="Steyskal, G. C. (1963) Taxonomic notes on Sciomyzidae (Diptera, Acalyptratae). Papers of the Michigan Academy of Science, Arts and Letters, 48, 113 - 125." type="journal article" year="1963">Steyskal (1963: fig. 1)</bibRefCitation>
, as in 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FEC8FD74FE54EDFC" authorityName="Rozkosny" authorityYear="1991" box="[362,493,711,735]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shatalkini">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FEC8FD74FE54EDFC" box="[362,493,711,735]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. shatalkini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(not figured by 
<bibRefCitation id="CA23B7EEFFFCFFE2FD38FD74FCFAEDFC" author="Rozkosny, R." box="[666,835,712,735]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" pagination="391 - 406" refId="ref2724" refString="Rozkosny, R. (1991) A key to the Palaearctic species of Pherbellia Robineau-Desvoidy, with descriptions of three new species (Diptera, Sciomyzidae). Acta Entomologica Bohemoslovaca, 88, 391 - 406." type="journal article" year="1991">Rozkošný 1991</bibRefCitation>
: figs 13, 14). In lateral view, the posterior surstylus in 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FA2AFD74FEB9EC22" authorityName="Rozkosny" authorityYear="1991" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shatalkini">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FA2AFD74FEB9EC22" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. shatalkini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is strongly indented beyond the basal 1/3 (figured as straight by 
<bibRefCitation id="CA23B7EEFFFCFFE2FC60FD56FBD7EC22" author="Rozkosny, R." box="[962,1134,746,769]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" pagination="391 - 406" refId="ref2724" refString="Rozkosny, R. (1991) A key to the Palaearctic species of Pherbellia Robineau-Desvoidy, with descriptions of three new species (Diptera, Sciomyzidae). Acta Entomologica Bohemoslovaca, 88, 391 - 406." type="journal article" year="1991">Rozkošný 1991</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 19) but is only slightly indented in 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FEB6FCB1FEC3EC07" authorityName="Steyskal" authorityYear="1963" box="[276,378,780,804]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frohnei">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FEB6FCB1FEC3EC07" box="[276,378,780,804]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. frohnei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The internal genitalia have not yet been described nor figured for 
<taxonomicName id="69B2B19CFFFCFFE2FBE7FCB1FB12EC07" authorityName="Steyskal" authorityYear="1963" box="[1093,1195,780,804]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frohnei">
<emphasis id="9CC6160DFFFCFFE2FBE7FCB1FB12EC07" box="[1093,1195,780,804]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. frohnei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
